    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen enabling `vim.lsp.inline_completion.enable` filtering on a specific client, after closing a fugitive commit buffer I get the following error:\n```\nError in InsertEnter Autocommands for \"*\":\nLua callback: ...tly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:217: Invalid buffer id: 3\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_clear_namespace'\n        ...tly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:217: in function 'hide'\n        ...tly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:166: in function 'show'\n        ...tly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:264: in function 'automatic_request'\n        ...tly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:48: in function <...tly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inline_completion.lua:47>\n```\n\nVery likely I've just misunderstood the API, but I wasn't certain so I wanted to raise a bug.\nOfc just close if you think this isn't relevant.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n<details><summary>minimal.lua</summary>\n\n```lua\n-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  -- ADD PLUGINS _NECESSARY_ TO REPRODUCE THE ISSUE, e.g:\n  'https://github.com/tpope/vim-fugitive',\n  'https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig',\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\n-- ADD INIT.LUA SETTINGS _NECESSARY_ FOR REPRODUCING THE ISSUE\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"LspAttach\", {\n  callback = function(args)\n    local bufnr = args.buf\n    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(args.data.client_id)\n    print(\"LSP started: \" .. client.name .. \" for buffer \" .. bufnr)\n    if client.supports_method(\"textDocument/inlineCompletion\") then\n      vim.lsp.inline_completion.enable(true, { client_id = client.id })\n      -- Enabling for a specific buffer fixes this issue\n      --vim.lsp.inline_completion.enable(true, { bufnr = bufnr })\n    end\n  end,\n})\n-- Enabling for all clients fixes this issue\n--vim.lsp.inline_completion.enable(true)\n\nvim.lsp.config(\"copilot\", {\n  -- Use whatever your install path is\n  cmd={\"/Users/osm/.local/share/nvim/mason/bin/copilot-language-server\", \"--stdio\"},\n})\nvim.lsp.enable(\"copilot\")\n```\n\n</details>\n\n1. Ensure you're using a nightly nvim + have `copilot-language-server` installed\n2. Run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua minimal.lua`\n3. Run `:CopilotSignIn` + verify that inline completion is working\n4. `:G init`\n5. `:G commit`\n6. `:q` (exit the buffer without editing or committing it)\n7. Attempt typing in the lua buffer\n\nAs mentioned in the `minimal.lua` you can resolve this by using either of the other two methods to enable inline completion.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nInline completion continues to work without error\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-nightly+ 24020ef\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.6.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix using github:nix-community/neovim-nightly-overlay",
